The funny thing. Nuance is so easily lost. Whatever I say about marriage is quite funny and probably taken the wrong way more often than not. I donâ€™t find the prison to be monogamy; not that at all. The aspect I find to seem a bit restricting at heart is 1. Paperwork (this is in order of importance). And 2. Just the idea of someone giving you credit or blame for their state of life or mind. (Whether good or bad; itâ€™s something no one else is ever qualified for being in charge.)

It really is that simple. Iâ€™m for monogamy, commitment & love, if those are desires one holds. I donâ€™t think those are pie in the sky or even that hard. ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ I feel that the constructs around it tend to, in some ways, eclipse the centrality and importance OF actual love and respect, etc. but they certainly all are not mutually exclusive and there are no hard and fast rules. 

Being with one person forever can be one of the most beautiful things and itâ€™s something I actually highly value when I see it done well. I think itâ€™s one of the greatest achievements in the world in some ways. But I feel the freedom of the individual must come first and all other things must come second to that and serve that sole higher purpose; whether it looks like marriage or not. Personally I feel like married life is more of a state of feeling and being than anything else. You just are that. Or youâ€™re not. Status is only whatever energy you are at any moment in time. But to be clear, relationships based on love and respect and integrity are always to be appreciated and valued and protected and invested in.

I have been experimenting â€¦ I sort of made it up or felt inspired to do it. Communicating beyond words. (Some people wish I would hurry that process along ğŸ¤ªğŸ˜‚ğŸ¤£ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£). Just a few.
We do it all of the time; communicate without words. Our energies are always in communication with those that we know, and even those that we donâ€™t.
Iâ€™ve been doing this, not to be experimental or weird, believe it or not, but because I found that the energies in some ways I was trying to convey to others, felt too much beyond the realm of the words, all to varying degrees in scope and complexity and grandeur. So sending them directly with energy packets of that light-encoded information just seemed the best way to go. It just occurred to me to start doing it on purpose the other day. Iâ€™ve done it before, more for personal use I guess you could say, with things I felt so deeply upon. But these new ones are more run of the mill sorts; itâ€™s like sending a package via the post. I will see how it goes. How well or viable of a data transmission this is. How much of the energy is captured or received by them. Just one of those random things I am working upon. I think also it came from having more people to visit with than perhaps I had the time, so it also seemed like if we are all busy, there is a way to be sending literal love and enjoyment together, at any time of the day, and thereby collapsing space and time.

I should addâ€¦ I did get dragged into a physical visit with someone I beyond beyond words deeply love andâ€¦ they are one of the very few people I always always feel was worth seeing in person. Every time. No fail. Soâ€¦ Iâ€™m not suggesting completely using this method over physical love or being together; but it does work well for acquaintances and the like or even very loved ones, in a pinch for time.

"Hello sir, what would you like today? I have different varieties of Aakukuralu(leafy vegetables). There's freshly picked Gongura, Thummi kura, Bacchala kura, Thota Kura with me. I also have some kothmir and karivepaku. 

I have been selling leafy vegetables for the last 40 years now. I am 57 years old. I studied till class five and might have continued studying but dropped out as there was no one to encourage me. I sometimes wonder how my life would have turned out if I did.

I started working when I was really young.  I got married at the age of 11 and that was the time my schooling stopped. Looking back, I cannot blame my parents as that was the situation back in our village. Thankfully, I was married to a  supportive and progressive man and he encouraged me to work even after marriage.  Unfortunately, he passed away three years ago due to kidney failure. 

At my age, when most lead a retired life, I chose to work hard for my survival. I plan my day's work accordingly. In the morning, from 5:30 to 9:30, I sell the vegetables by walking on the streets. I take a break for an hour and then go to the local government school to cook the mid-day meals. I go back home at 4 pm and finish my household works. In this way, I constantly keep myself occupied so that I could stay fit both physically and mentally and also support my family. 

Am I happy with my work? Of course, yes. I look for happiness in the little things. Every time I make a sale, I make sure I count it as a blessing. It makes me happy. Sure, not every day is a fruitful one or a day that goes according to my expectations.  But I believe that every morning is a fresh start; a fresh start to find happiness and opportunities all around me."

This #lucky #bamboo will survive. 
The parent bamboo had turned yellow. This sprout has a little bit of green left, so I cut it off and put it in water.

To my surprise roots were formed within 10days. I let the roots grow a bit long and then moved it to this soil medium. 

Why soil? Well water medium had too much maintenance. Change of water, algae cleaning and risk of spilling. 
Also while changing water, I tend to disturb it a lot. So soil medium suits well for me.

Plant: Lucky bamboo (well, that's what it is called. Not sure if it is a bamboo or not)

Yahhhh....bakal suram dramanya...

Drama baru 'Happiness' disutradarai oleh Ahn Gilho, ditulis oleh Han Sangwoon, dengan para pemainnya Han Hyojoo, Park Hyungsik, Jo Woojin, Lee Joonhyuk, Park Joohee, Baek Hyunjin, Park Hyungsoo, Bae Haesun, dan Cha Soonbae

Happiness' adalah drama thriller apocalypse saat penyakit menular sudah menjadi new normal di sebuah kompleks apartemen yang baru dibangun di kota besar dimana lantai atas dijual secara umum dan lantai bawah disewakan, muncul perang psikologis dan diskriminasi kelas. Kota itu hancur saat tanda-tanda kiamat menyerang berupa penyakit menular jenis baru yang membuat manusia sengsara.

'Happiness' akan tayang mulai 5 November menggantikan slot tayang 'Yumi's Cells' di tvN.

.
.
Meski kita menonton drama, tolong ya harus seimbang juga sama kewajiban, jangan lupa beribadah, belajar, selalu berbuat baik dan pekerjaan rumah harus dilakukan juga.

Bagi yang mau berpendapat, menambahkan, atau mengoreksi silahkan bisa di tulis di kolom komentar. Jangan lupa like, komen, save dan share ya...

The same measure that you love yourself is how you will love others. If you don't love yourself you will need people to love you and when they disappoint you then the whole bottom falls out cause now you don't feel loved again. If I love me and you don't love me I still feel loved. So if you keep your love from me, I'm still satisfied cause I loved me before you met me, so if you leave me I still love me. So the key is to fall in love with yourself first. That is why we are so difficult to others cause we're trying to get them to love us so we can feel loved. Thats why some say they've been manipulated by others. It's a sign of self hatred. You have to discover yourself or you will never feel loved. Self love is a result of self source. You can't love yourself if you don't know where you came from because source determines value. You will end up suffering from other people's value of you and that is why you will need them to keep giving you value or sometimes we create value out of the things we collect. That is why the fashion industry controls our lives which makes us broke and depressed because we keep buying things to give ourselves value cause you don't know how much you're worth. That is why when you lose them you really go crazy. When you realize how much you're worth, you will fall in love with yourself.

Time allows us to live life in seasons and enable us to manage destiny and days. You don't have to live your life all at once. Time provides opportunities to regulate choice and establish change. You can decide to do something different this year than you did last year. Time guarantees us that nothing in life last forever. There is a season for everything. If you try take things out of its season they will never work for you no matter what you do. Seasons bring their own inherent blessings. If you continue to study your season, everything will work in your favor. When its your season, even your enemies become your friends. Our destiny is determined by our decisions.

There is nothing more powerful than attitude. Attitude dictates your response to the present and it determines the quality of your future. Whatever you're experiencing, you do it through your attitude. Your attitude is you manifesting your true self. Our attitudes are the manifestation of our beliefs and convictions. Most times our belief holds us back. It does not matter what happens to you, what matters is how you handle it. Proverbs 23:7 always get misunderstood. The word 'Heart' has nothing to do with that organ in your chest. The word heart in the bible means your 'MIND'. But it's your sub conscious mind. The bible calls it the seat of reasoning. The heart(mind) is where you store everything that you come to believe. It is very dangerous to store them there cause they remain there for a long period of time and that's why it's called ' conditioning'. You condition your heart to accept certain things to be true, right and acceptable.You're not going to become what you heard, you're going to become what you stored.

Just in case you needed some thought-provoking journal entries...

Journaling is a great way to gain insight, vent, and express. We hold a lot in! Think about how many people will ask you 'how are you?', at some point today. And most of those times you will just say 'I'm good.'.

So if you have a busy schedule today and don't get much time to chat or process with others, process with your journal. Invite in a conversation with yourself and see where it takes you.

It's healthy to spend time with your thoughts and feelings; to connect with your hopes, dreams, fears and behaviors. Say hi and dive in!

Building a consistent journaling practice ğŸ“

If you have ever journaled before you will know how much it can benefit you by simply getting a pen to paper. 

Being consistent with journaling is where some people can struggle most, this is why it's important to try these useful tips.

1. Set a Goal for yourself as to why you have started journaling to keep you focused.
2. Dedication 5, 10, 15 minutes a day that you can commit to with no distractions.
3. Be present. This is your time to bring awareness to anything you are struggling with or to keep you on track to achieve your goals. It deserves your full attention.
4. Don't forget to reflect on your journaling journey. Often times we don't give ourselves enough credit for overcoming life's challenges and our life's achievements. Reflecting on our journey is a very important part of the process.

Following are helpful strategies gleaned from my personal experience and from my work with coaching clients who are burned out, growing cranky, frustrated and even depressed. These strategies immediately diminish feelings of being overwhelmed so you can refocus and make some work/life balance decisions.Â 

Stop what you are doing for a few minutes and take a break. Go for a short walk, sit outside under a tree, meditate, breathe deeply, go to a movie, call a friend to have coffee and share what is going on.Â 

Get a piece of paper and make two columns. In one column, list urgent things you need to do this week. In the other column, list those projects that you can delegate, hire or barter to be done.Â 

Eliminate, eliminate, eliminate. Unsubscribe to unnecessary e-mail, organize your desk and office to decrease clutter, stop attending meetings, get off committees and decrease volunteering at fundraisers unless you have a total passion for the organization and the cause.Â 

Do not spend time with people whom you do not like. Assess your friends and business colleagues. Do they support and honor who you are? If they are negative and donâ€™t share your vision for your dreams, donâ€™t spend another minute with them.Â 

Decide what is most important in your life. If you want a balanced life, you will have to make changes in your life to allow this to happen. That takes some time and planning but it will be well worth the improvement in your life!Â 

Take an action step today to make change in your life! Call a friend who will support you, take a class to get organized, or work with a coach who will support and motivate you to have a more balanced life.Â
